    "client_msg_id": "dc0950e4-2289-4efc-96dc-329c55a342dd",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I'm pretty excited about Verse's programming model. It supports the most interesting concepts from logic programming. For example, it's easy to express combinatorial searches, i.e. \"find all pairs/n-tuples of things that have a certain relationship\".\n\n(In a conventional PL, you'd usually have to write a nested loop — or use a library — to express the same thing.)",
